<p><em>Note: The Gladius is a double-edged sword, just a tad longer than the Khopesh. It was wielded by ancient Romans during the era where Rome conquered most of the Mediterranean. The only similarity I can see between the Khopesh and the Gladius is that both are swords. It could be random, but I'm theorizing that the connection is due to both weapons being wielded by the common soldier of the respective era and region. - Dr. Zavalosa</em></p>
